WEBVTT

00:02.018 --> 00:05.106
Thank you for downloading or streaming this message from Emmanuel Church.

00:05.527 --> 00:10.038
We are one church with multiple locations, and we believe God wants to bless you right where you are.

00:10.058 --> 00:16.434
In a few moments, you're going to hear some practical teaching from God's word that I believe will be inspiring and relevant to your life.

00:16.642 --> 00:28.134
First though, if you haven't yet experienced Immanuel Live, we encourage you to go to our website eclife.org to check out our service times and locations so that you can experience Immanuel in person or through our online campus.

00:28.835 --> 00:37.604
If this message blesses you and you'd like to support the ministry financially, again you can go to eclife.org and click on the giving tab and choose online campus at your campus.

00:38.285 --> 00:42.930
Thanks again for joining us today and we hope this message will be an encouragement to you on your spiritual journey.

00:43.906 --> 00:55.807
We are starting a brand new series and I always get kind of jazz and we get into some new content, but I'm especially excited today because we are talking about the mission of our church and why we exist as a church.

00:55.827 --> 01:08.370
So if you are here for the first time, if you're a guest with us today, you're gonna hear some things that really I think is a great, great for you to hear up for the first time being here because this is the stuff that if you cut us,

01:08.706 --> 01:10.548
Like, we bleed this stuff, okay?

01:10.569 --> 01:13.833
Like, this is like what we are all about as a church.

01:13.853 --> 01:24.728
And before we get into that, I just want to welcome everyone joining us at all of our campuses, our Franklin campus, our Band of Campus, our Garfield Park campus, of course here at Greenwood, everyone watching on our online campus and our micro sites.

01:24.788 --> 01:26.069
We welcome all of you.

01:26.870 --> 01:27.672
So exciting.

01:27.712 --> 01:32.498
We know if we've got friends watching all over the country and even over the world.

01:32.546 --> 01:34.468
Today is a good day for you to be joining us.

01:34.748 --> 01:37.290
Today we're starting a series called The Relentless Pursuit.

01:37.530 --> 01:41.374
And if you were here many years ago, you will recall that phrase.

01:41.454 --> 01:44.857
It's something that is near and dear to our heart.

01:44.937 --> 01:49.120
It's really what we are all about as a church and why we exist.

01:49.140 --> 01:53.644
Another way we say it is that we exist to see people come to Christ and grow in Christ.

01:53.704 --> 02:02.532
We are on a relentless pursuit to see our friends, our family members, our co-workers, hey, even strangers come and know Jesus Christ and enter

02:02.512 --> 02:04.177
into the kingdom of God.

02:04.217 --> 02:05.200
Where do we get this from?

02:05.220 --> 02:08.048
Where do we get this the clarity of our mission as a church?

02:08.108 --> 02:09.152
We get it from Jesus.

02:09.192 --> 02:11.378
We get it from how he lived his life.

02:11.490 --> 02:13.252
We get it from the things that he said.

02:13.392 --> 02:19.378
One day he was on the road walking past a guy named Levi, and Levi was simply doing his job.

02:19.418 --> 02:21.320
He was out there collecting taxes.

02:21.340 --> 02:22.040
That's what he did.

02:22.481 --> 02:26.325
And Jesus' message to him, if you're a notetaker, was so simple.

02:26.645 --> 02:27.786
Two words in your notes.

02:28.126 --> 02:30.629
Jesus' invitation to Matthew was so simple.

02:30.889 --> 02:33.231
He said, follow me.

02:34.352 --> 02:38.837
Just come on, just kind of get up from what you're doing and come follow me.

02:38.897 --> 02:40.018
Wasn't complicated.

02:40.482 --> 02:42.627
But it was significant.

02:42.647 --> 02:44.090
It was extraordinary.

02:44.110 --> 02:45.052
Let me explain why.

02:45.493 --> 02:50.425
Back in those days, for someone to follow a rabbi, and that's what Jesus was.

02:50.505 --> 02:51.467
He was a rabbi.

02:51.507 --> 02:52.990
He was a teacher of the law.

02:53.712 --> 02:58.162
In order to follow a rabbi, you had to be the cream of the crop.

02:58.850 --> 03:03.014
You had to go through years and years and years of education and schooling.

03:03.274 --> 03:09.941
You had to memorize the first five books of the Bible, the Pentateuch, Genesis, Exodus, Leviticus, Numbers, Deuteronomy.

03:09.961 --> 03:15.287
You had to be the best of the best of the best for a rabbi to come up to you and say, hey, guess what?

03:15.867 --> 03:16.548
You've made it.

03:17.048 --> 03:18.169
You're the cream of the crop.

03:18.330 --> 03:21.893
Now you can come follow me and be my disciple.

03:21.913 --> 03:26.738
And here's Jesus, like the greatest rabbi to ever live, and he stops

03:27.138 --> 03:31.543
to invite a tax collector who failed out of Jewish school.

03:32.163 --> 03:36.568
He was a total thief, because back in those days, it wasn't like working for the IRS.

03:38.330 --> 03:40.793
Basically, there were no rules, there were no regulations.

03:41.373 --> 03:43.235
You can charge whatever you wanted to charge.

03:43.976 --> 03:45.178
You could pocket the difference.

03:45.238 --> 03:46.960
Essentially, that's what the tax collectors did.

03:47.000 --> 03:52.946
They worked for the Roman government, and they would overcharge their friends, neighbors, family members,

03:53.442 --> 04:00.233
whatever they wanted, and they would pay the Roman government, and then they would take the difference without regulation, and they would put it in their pocket.

04:00.754 --> 04:03.278
And so tax collectors were the worst of the worst.

04:03.298 --> 04:08.908
They were put into this category of murderers and prostitutes, the scum of the earth.

04:09.508 --> 04:15.078
And here's Jesus, breaking protocol, walking up to the, not the cream of the crop, but the bottom of the barrel.

04:15.118 --> 04:20.146
And he says to him, you come follow me.

04:21.026 --> 04:33.139
This invitation is also incredibly significant because what it meant back then to follow a rabbi was that you left everything behind and you became this apprentice, this understudy, this student.

04:33.379 --> 04:34.741
You went where the rabbi went.

04:35.261 --> 04:36.443
You ate with the rabbi ate.

04:37.464 --> 04:40.387
You lived, sometimes you lived with the rabbi that you were studying under.

04:40.947 --> 04:45.672
This was a radical call of obedience to follow the rabbi.

04:45.712 --> 04:50.898
And Matthew makes this decision to get up.

04:51.554 --> 04:52.996
and follow Jesus.

04:53.016 --> 04:54.559
Look what it says in verse 28.

04:54.659 --> 04:56.943
Oh, I'm sorry, verse 28.

04:57.223 --> 05:00.308
Jesus says, so Levi got up and he left everything.

05:01.490 --> 05:03.313
And he followed Jesus.

05:05.376 --> 05:05.456
Wow.

05:05.476 --> 05:06.318
What's going on here?

05:06.919 --> 05:11.185
Well, Levi actually realizes what's at stake here.

05:11.205 --> 05:16.594
He realizes that this is an extraordinarily moment in his life to be invited to follow

05:16.674 --> 05:17.215
a rabbi.

05:17.295 --> 05:18.536
He knows he's a thief.

05:18.777 --> 05:20.178
He knows he's a crook.

05:20.198 --> 05:22.481
He knows that he's been chasing money.

05:23.562 --> 05:24.684
That's what these guys were doing.

05:25.244 --> 05:29.650
They were tax collectors were incredibly wealthy.

05:30.230 --> 05:34.996
The whole goal of their life was to accumulate wealth and buy things and have nice homes.

05:36.618 --> 05:42.405
And he suddenly sees something different, a different path, a different way to go.

05:42.525 --> 05:46.610
And maybe he's even heard about Jesus, that Jesus is full of grace.

05:47.202 --> 05:53.952
and mercy that Jesus will forgive the worst of the worst, that following Jesus led to peace and joy.

05:53.993 --> 05:57.438
And so he gets up and he follows.

05:58.399 --> 06:00.282
You know, there's a lot of gospels out there today.

06:01.204 --> 06:07.253
And the word gospel simply means good news or, you know, the path to go down for life.

06:07.473 --> 06:08.775
That's what the word gospel means.

06:09.356 --> 06:10.418
In our culture,

06:10.498 --> 06:12.823
Promises us all different types of gospels.

06:12.983 --> 06:14.807
It says, hey, if you pursue money, you'll be happy.

06:14.827 --> 06:16.711
If you pursue success, you'll be happy.

06:16.771 --> 06:19.496
If you have more stuff, you'll be happy.

06:20.038 --> 06:23.124
If you have a really great relationship, you'll be happy.

06:24.407 --> 06:29.016
There's a lot of things that our culture promises us happiness through.

06:29.838 --> 06:31.922
And Jesus says, no, no, no, listen, here's the deal.

06:32.034 --> 06:33.316
They're all wrong.

06:33.356 --> 06:35.740
That Levi, you've been going down the wrong path.

06:35.941 --> 06:37.223
You know it, and I know it.

06:37.283 --> 06:40.248
Levi, the money will never make you happy.

06:40.268 --> 06:42.512
Come follow me.

06:43.694 --> 06:46.599
And John 14 verse 6, the verse that we just skipped over right here.

06:46.639 --> 06:47.420
Look what Jesus said.

06:47.460 --> 06:55.474
He said, recorded by the apostle John, I am the way, I am the truth, and I am the saint with me, alive.

06:56.770 --> 07:02.797
See, a rabbi was claiming that you should follow me because I have discovered the path to true life.

07:03.158 --> 07:04.339
I am the way.

07:05.060 --> 07:10.266
Every single rabbi had an interpretation of the Pentateuch, Genesis, Exodus, Leviticus, Numbers, Deuteronomy.

07:10.787 --> 07:15.753
Every single rabbi was saying, look, my interpretation, my way is the best way.

07:15.873 --> 07:16.614
It's the truth.

07:16.754 --> 07:17.354
It's the life.

07:17.695 --> 07:20.338
Come follow and study under me.

07:20.866 --> 07:27.357
Jesus would say to us today, there's a lot of people out there claiming to know the way and the truth and the life, but they're all wrong.

07:28.960 --> 07:29.481
I am the way.

07:30.162 --> 07:32.005
I am the truth and I am the life.

07:32.426 --> 07:36.553
No one comes to the Father except through me.

07:37.915 --> 07:40.960
Wow, what an incredible invitation.

07:40.980 --> 07:46.610
And Matthew accepts, he gets up, he leaves behind his tax collecting booth and he follows Jesus

07:46.754 --> 07:49.741
And he becomes one of the most influential Christians of all time.

07:49.962 --> 07:51.746
He goes on to write the book of Matthew.

07:51.786 --> 07:53.170
His name is Matthew Levi.

07:53.250 --> 07:53.651
Same thing.

07:53.671 --> 07:54.453
I don't know how that works.

07:54.533 --> 07:56.818
You can Google it.

07:56.838 --> 07:57.500
It's the same dude.

07:57.741 --> 07:58.382
It's the same dude.

07:58.422 --> 08:00.106
He writes the Gospel of Matthew.

08:00.327 --> 08:04.978
He records the Sermon on the Mount, the greatest TED talk ever given, 17 minutes long.

08:07.106 --> 08:08.468
He follows around Jesus.

08:08.488 --> 08:12.072
He memorizes his talks and he records what he hears.

08:12.133 --> 08:17.680
Matthew chapter 4 verse 17, this is the message that Jesus would go around and he would preach.

08:17.720 --> 08:24.949
He would say, repent of your sins and turn to God for the kingdom of heaven is near.

08:25.450 --> 08:28.454
That was the message that Jesus gave when he would start preaching.

08:29.215 --> 08:31.698
How different that is from what we hear preachers say today.

08:32.450 --> 08:36.174
A lot of times you hear the gospel, you wanna know what the good news is?

08:36.575 --> 08:38.116
That Jesus has come to this earth.

08:38.196 --> 08:39.678
He's died in a cross three days later.

08:39.718 --> 08:43.242
He rose from the grave and if you trust in him, you can go to heaven when you die.

08:43.262 --> 08:43.763
Have you heard of this?

08:44.824 --> 08:46.226
No, I don't disagree with any of that.

08:46.306 --> 08:47.066
I believe it's all true.

08:47.387 --> 08:48.949
But that's not what Jesus said.

08:50.350 --> 08:54.194
He didn't say when he started preaching in his ministry, hey, here's what's gonna happen.

08:54.455 --> 08:56.958
I'm gonna die on a cross three days later on a rise again.

08:56.998 --> 08:59.561
And if you trust in me, you get to go to heaven when you die.

08:59.761 --> 09:00.882
Isn't that awesome, guys?

09:01.410 --> 09:03.133
That wasn't his message.

09:03.153 --> 09:04.936
This is actually very different from that.

09:04.956 --> 09:05.316
Do you agree?

09:05.336 --> 09:05.817
Yes or no?

09:07.279 --> 09:13.569
Repent of your sins and turn into the kingdom of God because it's near.

09:14.230 --> 09:17.375
It's like the remote control when your kids haven't lost it, right?

09:17.716 --> 09:19.218
It's near.

09:20.162 --> 09:21.863
I lose it too, so I'm not just blaming them.

09:21.904 --> 09:26.668
But what it means to be near is that it's right there at hand and you can take hold of it and you can make use of it.

09:27.188 --> 09:29.590
It's not this far place off after you die.

09:30.051 --> 09:39.158
Many Christ followers today are under the, I don't know, delusion or delusion that Christianity is about the next life.

09:39.199 --> 09:41.440
Like things will be really good in the next life.

09:41.460 --> 09:46.805
There'll be no tears and no crime and no fear and no disease and no cancer and all that's true.

09:47.105 --> 09:50.148
But Jesus didn't say, hey, here's what I want you to do.

09:50.128 --> 09:51.691
Drag your feet through this life.

09:52.913 --> 09:53.675
Life's terrible.

09:54.356 --> 09:55.037
Life's hard.

09:56.079 --> 10:00.608
And just get excited about dying because then when you die, everything's going to be great.

10:01.570 --> 10:03.133
That wasn't his message, was it?

10:03.975 --> 10:07.922
Just kind of grind through this horrible, terrible existence on earth.

10:08.463 --> 10:12.050
And then when death happens, that's when the party begins.

10:13.122 --> 10:18.751
And that's a lot of how the average Christian is literally walking through their life, dragging their feet.

10:18.831 --> 10:29.048
Life is so hard and they're complaining and, oh, they got back pains and neck pains and I got this and no wonder the people around you don't want to become Christians.

10:29.889 --> 10:30.931
Like, who would want that?

10:31.572 --> 10:31.812
Right?

10:32.353 --> 10:35.218
Like, if that's what Christianity is for, like, I don't need God.

10:36.674 --> 10:43.222
Jesus' message wasn't about, hey, get excited about what happens after death, although there's some exciting stuff coming.

10:44.244 --> 10:46.567
His message was, no, I've come to bring heaven here.

10:46.627 --> 10:49.010
Right now, it's near.

10:49.050 --> 10:51.433
You can step into it right now.

10:52.654 --> 10:53.555
And here's how you do it.

10:53.776 --> 10:55.097
You have to repent.

10:56.019 --> 10:57.280
That's his message.

10:57.300 --> 10:58.121
What does it mean to repent?

10:58.422 --> 10:59.503
It means to simply turn.

11:00.244 --> 11:01.906
It means to do an about face.

11:02.754 --> 11:09.044
It means to do a 180 to see what's going on is that we are living in our own little kingdoms or kingdoms, ladies.

11:10.647 --> 11:11.728
We know about your kingdoms.

11:12.730 --> 11:13.631
I know about your kingdoms.

11:13.651 --> 11:14.553
I got two in my house.

11:16.796 --> 11:23.707
We have to turn from living in our own ways according to our own knowledge of what we think is right or wrong.

11:23.728 --> 11:27.794
And we have to start step into a different kingdom, which is God's kingdom.

11:28.802 --> 11:33.008
A couple years ago, Jackie and I took the kids down to Florida way down south somewhere.

11:33.028 --> 11:33.869
I think it was Orlando.

11:33.889 --> 11:36.113
It was like 18 hours to get there on the way back.

11:37.034 --> 11:39.538
We're about three hours into our trip.

11:39.558 --> 11:40.219
We needed gas.

11:40.239 --> 11:41.380
We pulled into a gas station.

11:42.121 --> 11:43.283
And I think we were taking 95.

11:43.483 --> 11:44.745
I think that's the route we were on.

11:44.765 --> 11:47.089
95 North coming back to Indiana.

11:48.090 --> 11:50.914
And we got back on the highway.

11:51.615 --> 11:53.618
We got back on 95 going the wrong way.

11:55.522 --> 12:00.690
And I'm driving, and Jackie's in the passenger seat, and I'm like, man, this looks familiar.

12:00.750 --> 12:03.174
I've seen that.

12:03.234 --> 12:04.857
Everything just looks the same.

12:04.897 --> 12:06.679
It's amazing how Florida is like that.

12:07.360 --> 12:11.887
And then a little bit further, I'm like, oh, oh no.

12:13.250 --> 12:15.112
We're going the wrong way.

12:16.154 --> 12:17.456
Now, can I ask you a question?

12:17.777 --> 12:18.918
Just trimming you.

12:19.139 --> 12:21.062
Just like that's true.

12:22.664 --> 12:23.826
Whose fault does that?

12:25.282 --> 12:27.144
I mean, I'm the driver.

12:27.204 --> 12:28.947
Who's the navigator?

12:31.970 --> 12:32.151
Right?

12:34.453 --> 12:35.995
How much can one person do here?

12:36.035 --> 12:41.683
It's not, it wasn't Jackie's fault.

12:41.763 --> 12:43.265
It's just a little insight, man.

12:43.305 --> 12:44.766
It's always your fault, always.

12:46.088 --> 12:47.970
That's going to go a long way for some of you guys.

12:48.211 --> 12:49.092
Good marital advice.

12:49.192 --> 12:50.834
It's always your fault.

12:52.770 --> 12:54.913
But here's what we had to do on the highway that day.

12:54.953 --> 12:56.796
We had to repent.

13:00.502 --> 13:00.843
We did.

13:00.883 --> 13:03.968
We did a 180.

13:04.008 --> 13:04.789
We turned around.

13:05.550 --> 13:20.754
Jesus' message is that you are going the wrong way in selfishness and pride, in lust and arrogance and anger, and you have to turn and live in my kingdom.

13:21.410 --> 13:25.335
That was his message, and that's exactly what Matthew did.

13:26.377 --> 13:27.899
But that doesn't explain what the kingdom is.

13:28.900 --> 13:29.901
What is the kingdom?

13:29.921 --> 13:32.645
What does this offer come follow me into the kingdom?

13:32.685 --> 13:34.507
Well, if you're taking notes, it's real simple.

13:35.228 --> 13:38.513
The kingdom of God is the active rule of Jesus on earth.

13:39.934 --> 13:43.639
Remember, it's not about going to heaven when you die, although that's included.

13:43.659 --> 13:46.763
It's about the kingdom coming here right now.

13:47.004 --> 13:48.786
Think about the prayer that Jesus gave us.

13:49.314 --> 13:54.061
If you have some Catholic background and you grew up in Catholic church or went to Catholic school, you can quote this.

13:54.842 --> 13:56.524
Most of us can have heard it many, many times.

13:57.065 --> 13:57.706
You can say it with me.

13:58.286 --> 14:01.591
Our father, who art in heaven, hallowed be your name.

14:02.032 --> 14:03.594
Your kingdom come.

14:04.195 --> 14:05.797
Your will be done.

14:06.157 --> 14:15.750
Where on earth, as it is done in, that's not a prayer that he gave us to kind of say in church.

14:17.313 --> 14:18.354
That's a life.

14:18.882 --> 14:19.983
That's the message.

14:20.404 --> 14:23.608
God, today I want your kingdom here.

14:23.628 --> 14:34.461
I want your will, not my will, but your will to be done right now in this classroom, at the job, in this building, in this meeting when I'm parenting these children, when I'm having a discussion with my wife.

14:35.082 --> 14:37.124
I want your kingdom here now.

14:37.245 --> 14:37.765
And guess what?

14:37.785 --> 14:38.666
It's available now.

14:40.449 --> 14:44.914
Jesus brought the, He was the kingdom bringer to you and I.

14:45.730 --> 14:46.411
What is the kingdom?

14:46.711 --> 14:48.874
It's what God is doing on earth right now.

14:49.975 --> 15:00.306
So when you open up the New Testament and you see Jesus, he holds somebody like a leper or give somebody a blind person their sight or raise a little girl from the dead or whatever he was doing, that's the kingdom.

15:01.308 --> 15:05.412
The kingdom is wherever God is doing what God wants to do.

15:05.452 --> 15:06.153
Isn't that a kingdom?

15:06.173 --> 15:07.394
I mean, think about it with me.

15:07.414 --> 15:08.456
What's the nature of a kingdom?

15:08.496 --> 15:10.578
The kingdom or a kingdom, ladies?

15:11.458 --> 15:12.680
means you're in charge of what?

15:12.980 --> 15:14.322
This area right here.

15:14.702 --> 15:19.469
In other words, your will is executed over a certain area, right?

15:19.890 --> 15:22.593
Even if it's just your bedroom, right?

15:22.653 --> 15:23.555
Everybody's got in there.

15:23.575 --> 15:26.238
Like little children coming to this world, little kings and little queens.

15:27.019 --> 15:27.680
How do we know that?

15:27.900 --> 15:30.624
Two words, they learn, know where they learn that.

15:31.505 --> 15:32.226
It's built into them.

15:32.427 --> 15:33.648
And mine, right?

15:33.688 --> 15:34.930
Those are kingdom words.

15:35.458 --> 15:36.839
No and mine, right?

15:37.120 --> 15:39.682
Even if it's just their space in the back seat, right?

15:39.702 --> 15:43.846
They'll get into a fight with their brother or sister because their space was invaded.

15:44.687 --> 15:45.929
See, that's kingdom language.

15:48.831 --> 15:50.673
Kingdom is where God is doing things.

15:50.753 --> 15:54.797
One time Jesus cast a demon out of somebody in Luke chapter 11.

15:55.358 --> 15:57.540
And his critics said, oh, look, he's a devil.

15:58.201 --> 15:59.202
Only a devil can do that.

15:59.222 --> 16:01.364
And Jesus is like, come on, the devils don't cast out.

16:01.424 --> 16:02.625
Devils, they're on the same team.

16:02.685 --> 16:03.346
Knucklehead.

16:03.970 --> 16:05.211
That's my paraphrase, okay?

16:07.253 --> 16:08.755
And then Jesus says this in verse 20.

16:09.976 --> 16:12.618
But if I'm casting out demons by the power of who?

16:13.339 --> 16:18.524
God, like if God has showed up here, showed up here, then guess what?

16:18.784 --> 16:21.327
Then the kingdom has arrived.

16:22.028 --> 16:23.689
It's not out there after you die.

16:23.889 --> 16:24.730
It's right here.

16:24.991 --> 16:29.215
Like the kingdom is wherever Jesus decides to do anything.

16:31.137 --> 16:32.658
And then he says to you and I, come.

16:33.570 --> 16:35.792
and follow me into that kingdom.

16:36.894 --> 16:38.836
Live in it with me.

16:39.517 --> 16:40.438
Wow.

16:40.458 --> 16:43.061
That's the offer of Christianity.

16:43.801 --> 16:45.363
That's the invitation of Jesus.

16:45.403 --> 16:49.147
And I'm here to tell you, if you're a note taker, there's nothing like it on planet Earth.

16:49.287 --> 16:57.096
Life in the kingdom is the best offer for you and I on this globe that we live on.

16:58.117 --> 17:00.059
There is nothing better.

17:00.340 --> 17:02.482
Look, Levi was chasing money.

17:04.194 --> 17:04.895
And he saw it.

17:06.077 --> 17:07.719
He's like, money can do a little bit.

17:07.800 --> 17:08.641
It can make you a little happy.

17:08.661 --> 17:09.522
You can buy a lot of stuff.

17:09.863 --> 17:11.766
But this guy's got something else.

17:13.188 --> 17:14.770
What's going on with Kanye West right now?

17:14.911 --> 17:15.692
Come on, come on.

17:15.712 --> 17:16.733
You have to speed with Kanye.

17:17.334 --> 17:18.917
Like, I know, I was a critic at first.

17:18.937 --> 17:21.340
I was like, okay, let's see what this guy's doing.

17:21.360 --> 17:22.462
You know, he's a little bonkers.

17:24.145 --> 17:27.570
But now after you watch a little bit, he's holding church services.

17:28.162 --> 17:43.141
With like 15,000, I think he's renting space and 17,000 people show up and they're, he's preaching the gospel and people are coming to Christ and he's giving, he's making Christian music and he's, I think he's gonna be at Joel Osteen's church this weekend.

17:43.241 --> 17:50.310
He was just at a jail, I saw him preaching in a jail, rapping and doing music for prisoners and giving the gospel presentation and they're on their knees except in Christ.

17:51.892 --> 17:53.234
Why would Kanye do that?

17:53.890 --> 17:57.817
He's got Bentley's and private airplanes and mansions and he's married to Kim, right?

17:57.837 --> 17:59.320
Like, what does he need?

18:00.722 --> 18:02.185
Why would he turn to Christ?

18:02.265 --> 18:03.608
Why would he turn into the kingdom?

18:04.128 --> 18:11.682
Is it because he knows I've tasted all of it and the best deal on planet Earth is the kingdom?

18:11.702 --> 18:12.103
Yes or no?

18:14.688 --> 18:16.050
That's what's going on.

18:18.242 --> 18:20.185
Listen, there are desires inside of you.

18:20.225 --> 18:23.792
There are desires inside of me that nothing physical can ever satisfy.

18:23.812 --> 18:24.032
C.S.

18:24.212 --> 18:25.314
Lewis helped me to see this.

18:26.156 --> 18:29.742
In his book, Mirror Christianity, this is what he said, perhaps the best quote in the book.

18:30.062 --> 18:37.255
He said, if I find in myself a desire that nothing in this world, no experience in this world can satisfy the most probable explanation as I was made for what?

18:37.596 --> 18:38.297
Another world.

18:38.717 --> 18:39.379
What world is that?

18:39.679 --> 18:41.362
It's the kingdom of God.

18:42.722 --> 18:50.674
I love what St. Augustine said in the same vein, listen to what he said, you have made us for yourself, oh Lord, and our hearts are restless until they find rest in you.

18:51.395 --> 18:56.803
Like God, there's nothing in this world, no amount of money, no amount of success, no amount of fame, no fortune.

18:57.965 --> 19:02.512
There's nothing I can experience on this planet that can satisfy the desires of my soul.

19:02.812 --> 19:03.954
I tried when I was in high school.

19:03.974 --> 19:04.815
This is my story.

19:05.136 --> 19:06.738
This is why I'm a pastor today.

19:07.522 --> 19:24.082
When I was 16, 17, 18, all I wanted to do was be happy, and I thought, man, maybe if I'm the most popular kid, maybe that, maybe that, because I was a popular kid, and I was funny, and I did risky things, and I got people's respect, and I had a pretty girlfriend, and this, and then I got a car, and I was like, maybe it's sports.

19:24.322 --> 19:24.943
Maybe it's sports.

19:25.003 --> 19:35.115
So if I can dedicate myself to being the best basketball player I can be, then maybe that will satisfy this hunger for acceptance and happiness.

19:35.155 --> 19:36.277
And so I did it.

19:36.297 --> 19:38.059
I went after it and I practiced.

19:38.319 --> 19:40.242
And I broke the scoring record in my high school.

19:40.262 --> 19:41.643
I scored over 1,000 points.

19:41.683 --> 19:43.566
I made a short list of players in New York City.

19:44.026 --> 19:46.509
I made the New York Daily News Advance All Stars.

19:46.890 --> 19:48.031
My picture was in the paper.

19:48.311 --> 19:50.835
I was recruited by New York University to play basketball.

19:50.855 --> 19:52.777
I played basketball for them my freshman year.

19:53.017 --> 19:53.618
And I'm like,

19:54.626 --> 19:55.267
I'm still empty.

19:56.929 --> 19:57.610
All the success.

19:58.251 --> 19:58.972
I won the awards.

19:59.212 --> 19:59.953
I got the trophies.

20:01.035 --> 20:01.475
Well, then what?

20:01.655 --> 20:02.376
Maybe it's money.

20:02.577 --> 20:08.385
And right before I could start to pursue money, I stumbled into something called the kingdom of God.

20:09.987 --> 20:12.270
And it satisfied me in a way that nothing else could.

20:13.712 --> 20:16.095
And it's why I'm a pastor today.

20:17.537 --> 20:21.362
There's nothing better than the kingdom of God on this planet.

20:21.762 --> 20:25.286
Some of you have been chasing other things and you know it, you know it.

20:26.207 --> 20:27.689
It's not the next relationship.

20:28.270 --> 20:29.892
It's not the next raise.

20:31.074 --> 20:32.435
It's not the next promotion.

20:33.436 --> 20:34.518
It's not the different job.

20:34.598 --> 20:35.719
It's not having the baby.

20:35.799 --> 20:37.001
It's not having another baby.

20:39.264 --> 20:41.707
It's the kingdom that you were created for.

20:42.428 --> 20:46.833
When I meet people that are not in the kingdom, here's how I see them, not in a judgmental way.

20:48.155 --> 20:50.898
I see them as fish out of water.

20:53.122 --> 21:02.138
flopping around, still alive, but choking as they pursue money flopping around.

21:02.539 --> 21:04.743
You ever see a fish out of the water?

21:04.763 --> 21:05.985
It takes them a while to die.

21:06.025 --> 21:07.087
They're not dead yet.

21:07.127 --> 21:10.193
They're searching, looking, hoping.

21:11.615 --> 21:14.741
And what I try to do when I meet somebody like that, I was like, get in the water.

21:15.843 --> 21:17.586
Come on, follow Jesus.

21:17.730 --> 21:18.571
Dive into the kingdom.

21:18.731 --> 21:25.398
Like you were made to swim and live in the kingdom of God and thrive and find life in the water.

21:26.420 --> 21:34.328
One time Jesus said, I am the living water.

21:34.348 --> 21:34.428
Wow.

21:34.448 --> 21:36.531
He used provocative language when it came to the kingdom.

21:36.551 --> 21:38.973
Like no one tried to sell this deal harder than Jesus.

21:39.594 --> 21:40.535
Let me show you what I'm talking about.

21:40.935 --> 21:45.260
Levi records these words, interesting, in Matthew chapter 13 verse 44.

21:45.581 --> 21:46.962
Listen to what Jesus said about the kingdom.

21:47.138 --> 21:48.941
He said, the kingdom of heaven is like a what?

21:48.961 --> 21:50.643
Like a treasure.

21:51.965 --> 21:53.267
You know, pirates booty.

21:54.088 --> 21:59.756
You know, it's like the kingdom is like stumbling upon buried treasure.

22:00.658 --> 22:01.198
That's what he says.

22:01.980 --> 22:06.126
As the person's like plowing the field, digging in the field, he discovers this treasure.

22:06.206 --> 22:06.827
And what does he do?

22:07.267 --> 22:08.209
In his, watch this.

22:08.429 --> 22:09.250
In his, what?

22:09.270 --> 22:10.452
In his excitement.

22:10.572 --> 22:11.954
Another version says joy.

22:12.738 --> 22:15.923
He goes off and he sells everything he has.

22:15.983 --> 22:17.566
Well, first thing he does is he buries it.

22:17.586 --> 22:18.668
He's like, I'll hide this.

22:18.828 --> 22:19.670
All anybody else to find it.

22:20.451 --> 22:23.797
Then he gets all his stuff and he goes to eBay and he sells it all on eBay.

22:25.359 --> 22:28.705
And he gets enough money to come back and buy the field because what's in the field?

22:30.267 --> 22:31.990
I mean, I know it's plastic, but it's the best we can do.

22:34.194 --> 22:34.855
What's in the field?

22:35.256 --> 22:36.658
He found the treasure.

22:37.122 --> 22:40.505
He's like, I've got to get, this is Jesus teaching about the kingdom.

22:40.525 --> 22:45.771
Like this is what I came to bring this kingdom and you are made for it, it's treasure.

22:46.331 --> 22:50.796
Do whatever you have to do to gain it because it's that valuable.

22:50.816 --> 22:55.681
And so he goes off and he sells everything he owns to buy that field.

22:55.741 --> 22:57.142
Could you get more provocative than that?

22:57.903 --> 22:59.424
Could you sell it any more than that?

23:00.165 --> 23:02.167
It's the best offer on the planet.

23:02.207 --> 23:03.769
So let's talk about Levi.

23:03.789 --> 23:05.010
Levi stumbles in.

23:05.410 --> 23:06.552
He follows Jesus.

23:06.852 --> 23:08.434
We got some gold down here.

23:08.454 --> 23:09.496
It's going to distract me.

23:10.117 --> 23:14.042
Get that, get that.

23:14.062 --> 23:15.484
Levi, he gets up.

23:15.865 --> 23:17.427
He realizes what he's found.

23:17.908 --> 23:19.890
He's been invited into something grand.

23:19.931 --> 23:21.353
Something as hard as always long for.

23:21.433 --> 23:22.755
Something money could never give.

23:22.975 --> 23:25.438
Let me say that again, something money could never give.

23:25.518 --> 23:27.061
Some of you need to hear that twice.

23:29.324 --> 23:30.866
He leaves his job.

23:31.426 --> 23:32.809
He embraces the kingdom.

23:32.869 --> 23:33.891
He follows Christ.

23:34.031 --> 23:36.096
And then what does he do next?

23:36.116 --> 23:38.621
He does what is completely natural.

23:39.884 --> 23:44.012
Isn't it true that we invite others into what we enjoy?

23:46.998 --> 23:47.500
Isn't it true?

23:50.205 --> 23:50.987
Look what he does.

23:51.047 --> 23:52.530
Look what he does in verse 29.

23:52.834 --> 23:55.819
Later Levi held a banquet in his home with Jesus as the honored guest.

23:56.319 --> 24:04.272
Many of Levi's fellow tax collectors and other guests, other disreputable, other scum of the earth.

24:06.135 --> 24:06.475
Join.

24:08.278 --> 24:08.639
What did he do?

24:08.819 --> 24:11.343
He said, guys, I'm having a party at my house Friday night.

24:12.244 --> 24:12.845
You got to come.

24:13.186 --> 24:15.189
I want you to meet somebody.

24:17.673 --> 24:18.354
I want you to

24:18.434 --> 24:19.976
I want you to find what I've found."

24:19.996 --> 24:21.317
You notice this guy?

24:21.638 --> 24:23.900
This guy's got joy I've never seen.

24:23.920 --> 24:24.501
He's got peace.

24:25.062 --> 24:25.903
He's got grace.

24:25.983 --> 24:30.869
I know all the other teachers of the law that they hate us and we steal and we're bad people.

24:31.049 --> 24:33.692
But Jesus, when he saw me, he invited me in.

24:34.313 --> 24:35.174
Like, he gave me grace.

24:35.414 --> 24:35.975
You got to meet him.

24:36.736 --> 24:37.557
We're not too far gone.

24:38.778 --> 24:39.839
There's grace available for us.

24:40.240 --> 24:41.341
Will you come to my house Friday night?

24:41.441 --> 24:42.162
He throws a party.

24:43.170 --> 24:43.390
Why?

24:43.591 --> 24:46.235
Because it's natural for you and I to invite others into what we enjoy.

24:46.275 --> 24:47.056
Isn't this the way it works?

24:47.537 --> 24:50.862
You go to a nice restaurant, you eat some meal, and you get great service.

24:50.902 --> 24:51.283
What do you do?

24:51.523 --> 24:52.124
You post it.

24:53.587 --> 24:55.770
Some of you even take pictures of your food, and you post your food.

24:55.790 --> 24:58.875
Look, I think that's lame, but hey, you know what?

24:58.895 --> 24:59.336
It's human.

24:59.516 --> 25:00.217
I understand it.

25:00.277 --> 25:00.818
I think it's lame.

25:00.878 --> 25:01.419
I understand it.

25:01.439 --> 25:02.761
It's like, oh, I got to take a picture of this.

25:02.781 --> 25:03.502
Send it to my friends.

25:05.185 --> 25:05.906
Why do we do that?

25:06.818 --> 25:08.800
Because we want to share what we enjoy.

25:09.221 --> 25:10.282
We hear a great song.

25:10.302 --> 25:11.023
We want to share it.

25:11.223 --> 25:12.925
We see a funny video.

25:12.945 --> 25:14.026
Oh, this one gets me every time.

25:14.267 --> 25:16.289
When I see a funny video, I'm like, I'm cracking up.

25:16.349 --> 25:17.250
I have to tell my wife.

25:17.270 --> 25:17.931
I feel like I can't.

25:17.951 --> 25:19.192
It's like, you have to see this video.

25:19.212 --> 25:20.434
Come, stop what you're doing right now.

25:20.934 --> 25:21.555
Come in there.

25:21.575 --> 25:23.197
Come over here and watch this video.

25:23.217 --> 25:26.200
And if she's not available, I'll drag one of my kids in and say, you got to see.

25:26.401 --> 25:27.602
Look, say, watch this cat.

25:27.802 --> 25:28.623
You got to watch this cat.

25:28.864 --> 25:29.544
You're not going to believe it.

25:30.225 --> 25:30.986
Why do we do that?

25:33.108 --> 25:33.309
Right?

25:33.629 --> 25:34.450
You do it too.

25:35.138 --> 25:39.324
We do that because it's natural for you and I to invite others into what we enjoy.

25:39.845 --> 25:43.349
So here's Levi, like he has met God.

25:44.531 --> 25:47.595
He has tasted grace, amazing grace.

25:47.876 --> 25:51.561
He has found joy and peace that he's never known before.

25:52.442 --> 25:54.285
And he's like, guys, guys, guys, guys, guys, you gotta come.

25:56.107 --> 25:56.668
I love what C.S.

25:56.708 --> 25:58.450
Lewis said.

25:58.470 --> 26:03.197
The delight isn't complete until it's expressed.

26:03.217 --> 26:04.018
It's human.

26:04.194 --> 26:05.515
to share what we enjoy.

26:05.556 --> 26:17.289
In fact, when you experience something wonderful or delightful or tasty or joyful, and then you can't share it, isn't it frustrating?

26:18.030 --> 26:19.051
Don't you just want to go crazy?

26:19.551 --> 26:20.973
It's like, oh, I've got to tell somebody.

26:21.033 --> 26:27.220
Because the delight is incomplete until it's expressed.

26:27.240 --> 26:28.882
I am a pastor today.

26:29.410 --> 26:33.416
Not because a pastor is a great profession.

26:33.637 --> 26:34.238
I think it is.

26:35.540 --> 26:42.631
But I'm a pastor today because the delight is incomplete until it's expressed.

26:42.651 --> 26:47.979
It brings me incredible joy to talk about Jesus in the kingdom.

26:49.261 --> 26:52.847
Because I have found the treasure hidden in the field.

26:53.808 --> 26:57.554
And in my excitement and in my joy, I have done whatever I've had to do.

26:58.146 --> 27:01.551
to live in it and bathe in it and soak in it.

27:02.372 --> 27:05.736
And I just want you to taste what I've tasted.

27:07.338 --> 27:11.904
There's another person in our church that has experienced this.

27:12.565 --> 27:13.266
Her name is Cindy.

27:13.947 --> 27:15.409
And I want you to hear her story right now.

27:16.250 --> 27:19.615
It's a story of coming into the kingdom and inviting others in.

27:19.915 --> 27:20.676
Check out her story.

27:24.902 --> 27:27.986
It's like when we go in and the row keeps getting more full.

27:28.898 --> 27:33.364
And I don't know who those people are, and then all of a sudden I ask, and they go, oh, that's my cousin.

27:33.525 --> 27:34.586
Oh, that's my sister-in-law.

27:34.786 --> 27:38.792
Oh, that's my sister-in-law's mom, through their family, through their friends.

27:38.892 --> 27:39.974
It just keeps going.

27:43.219 --> 27:47.164
My name is Cindy Bailey, and I've been attending a manual church for about four and a half years.

27:48.286 --> 27:56.658
The story behind me starting to attend a manual was back in the spring of 2016 when my son, Alex,

27:56.834 --> 28:00.759
had asked if he could have a bachelor party at our house that we had just moved to.

28:01.800 --> 28:04.183
And I said, yes, as long as you stay in the garage.

28:04.763 --> 28:12.232
So he and a bunch of his high school buddies decided that they wanted to have a video party where they were going to play video games that they used to play in high school.

28:12.293 --> 28:17.038
So they put up a bunch of TVs in the garage and they were all out there having a good time.

28:17.058 --> 28:20.242
In fact, they were all screaming like little girls.

28:20.386 --> 28:28.217
When I went out to kind of see what the guys were doing, I just started having conversations with each one of them since I'd known them for so many years.

28:28.978 --> 28:31.982
And one of those friends was actually Ross Mills.

28:32.463 --> 28:35.567
And if you know him, he's one of the drummers on the worship team.

28:36.428 --> 28:40.875
And that was the night that Ross gave the invitation to me to come to church.

28:41.696 --> 28:43.358
And I said, well, we've got plans this weekend.

28:43.378 --> 28:45.722
And he said, well, I'm drumming next weekend.

28:45.762 --> 28:46.503
Who could you come?

28:46.543 --> 28:48.946
And I said, yeah, I'll be there.

28:49.634 --> 28:54.101
At that time, my husband Tom and I were going through a little bit of a rough season.

28:54.502 --> 28:59.410
His mom had been ill and we were also preparing for my dad to move in with us.

28:59.490 --> 29:01.955
He was starting to show signs of dementia.

29:02.375 --> 29:05.661
We knew that we had really some struggles ahead.

29:06.142 --> 29:13.554
When I took that invitation and I showed up that next weekend, the message that Danny was preaching was just on point for me.

29:13.666 --> 29:22.578
He really sent the message that we really cannot reach the potential that we are intended to reach without walking that walk with Jesus.

29:23.139 --> 29:27.725
And so from that point forward, I knew that I was just going to jump head first right into it.

29:28.466 --> 29:31.830
I was relentless to try and get my husband to come to church with me.

29:32.571 --> 29:33.493
And it took a while.

29:33.893 --> 29:35.896
First of all, I started going to church by myself.

29:36.216 --> 29:41.904
And every weekend that I went, I would just be fueled even more than I was the weekend before.

29:41.944 --> 29:43.346
So I knew

29:43.490 --> 29:48.436
that at that time I had a calling and I was intended to do more than just sit in a seat.

29:49.037 --> 29:53.642
That invitation is what changed everything for us individually and for our marriage.

29:54.503 --> 30:06.217
My husband and I started attending together and the longer that we started going to services, the more we realized that we needed to spread this message because we wanted to share the joy that we were feeling.

30:06.858 --> 30:08.760
So we started making invitations.

30:09.121 --> 30:13.426
This year I was blessed with the opportunity to join the worship team.

30:13.570 --> 30:17.534
where that's just given me another avenue for me to reach people.

30:18.255 --> 30:20.758
I get fueled when I've made those invitations.

30:20.818 --> 30:34.673
My husband and I have been to a restaurant or we drive through Starbucks or we're at the Lowe's or the Home Depot, you know, wherever we might be and we run into someone and we find that there's somebody that we feel like, you know, it would be somebody we can invite to church.

30:35.193 --> 30:43.442
I'll be up singing and I look across the congregation and all of a sudden I connect with a face and it's somebody that we invited.

30:43.586 --> 30:51.794
And I have to sometimes get myself together because I get overwhelmed that they accepted that invitation and they're actually sitting in one of those seats.

30:52.595 --> 30:54.016
We might not hit everybody.

30:54.257 --> 30:58.421
We might not, you know, bat a thousand, but we're gonna keep trying.

30:58.841 --> 31:05.408
We're gonna keep inviting because overall God left the 99 behind to seek out the one.

31:05.908 --> 31:08.130
And we feel like that we're on that pursuit as well.

31:08.751 --> 31:11.794
Sometimes you never know when somebody's hurting

31:12.034 --> 31:19.645
or somebody just needs that nudge and maybe we're that person that gets them to say, I'll show up.

31:20.707 --> 31:29.019
And to think that one invitation that I got from Ross hadn't happened.

31:29.039 --> 31:30.682
I don't want someone just to show up.

31:31.203 --> 31:41.618
I want somebody to show up and have that same experience that my husband and I had that have changed us individually and changed us as

31:41.762 --> 31:42.383
as a couple.

31:42.944 --> 31:49.513
I also see what it did for our friends who we've invited, what it's done to them individually, what it's done to their marriage.

31:50.274 --> 31:51.435
I'm in awe sometimes.

31:52.016 --> 31:59.727
When I look down the row and I'm like, okay, there was just four of us, now there's six of us, now there's eight of us, now there's 10 of us.

32:00.328 --> 32:02.130
And where does it end?

32:02.831 --> 32:04.654
It doesn't have to, right?

32:04.674 --> 32:05.375
It doesn't have to end.

32:06.136 --> 32:10.482
Because we can keep making invitations and those people that have accepted those invitations

32:10.786 --> 32:12.207
keep making invitations.

32:12.728 --> 32:18.734
And those people keep making invitations, and before you know it, there's not a seat left in the church.

32:19.795 --> 32:20.395
That's my hope.

32:29.925 --> 32:37.332
My favorite line, you said so many good things in that video, Cindy, but my favorite thing that you said was, I don't want people to just come sit.

32:37.352 --> 32:39.474
I want them to experience.

32:39.554 --> 32:41.697
what Tom and I have experienced.

32:41.717 --> 32:52.512
And what she's talking about is everything I've been trying to, to the best of my ability explained, life with God, purpose and meaning and joy and peace, like you've never known before.

32:53.193 --> 32:59.602
The satisfaction of your soul that nothing in this world could provide for you.

33:00.624 --> 33:01.946
Jesus says, come follow me.

33:01.986 --> 33:07.794
But you know that day, not everybody was excited about this little party that masked you through.

33:08.738 --> 33:10.000
There's some people that didn't like it.

33:10.640 --> 33:12.322
The Pharisees and the teachers of the law.

33:12.362 --> 33:16.047
Let me show you what they said in verse 30, Matthew chapter five.

33:16.107 --> 33:21.594
But the Pharisees and the teachers of the law, they complained that Jesus' disciples, they're like, why does he do this?

33:22.315 --> 33:24.137
Why does he eat with such scum?

33:26.800 --> 33:34.770
Their view of God was that all he had for sinners was wrath and indignation and anger and punishment.

33:35.618 --> 33:37.681
They didn't interpret the Old Testament correctly.

33:37.781 --> 33:43.069
All they had to do was read the book of Jonah to realize that God delights the show mercy, not judgment.

33:44.251 --> 33:47.456
If people would just turn, he's so quick to forgive.

33:47.596 --> 33:49.399
He's so longing to forgive.

33:51.542 --> 33:53.064
Why does he eat with such scum?

33:53.124 --> 33:54.487
So Jesus has to clarify.

33:54.527 --> 34:00.896
And the next thing he says in Matthew chapter four, five could be the vision statement of our church.

34:00.956 --> 34:02.098
It's just a little bit too long.

34:02.626 --> 34:03.487
But let me read it to you.

34:03.687 --> 34:05.729
He says to these guys, oh, you're so misled.

34:05.769 --> 34:11.114
Listen, don't you understand that healthy people don't need a doctor, but sick people do?

34:12.395 --> 34:19.962
Sinners, broken people, every single one of us, Levi, we are Levi.

34:21.043 --> 34:22.865
Don't you understand that?

34:22.885 --> 34:29.311
He says this, I have come not to call those who think they're righteous, because nobody is.

34:30.552 --> 34:32.434
You're misled if you think that you're

34:32.802 --> 34:34.204
righteous and better than others.

34:34.705 --> 34:35.406
We're all broken.

34:35.807 --> 34:39.313
But rather, I've come for those who know that they are sinners and need to do what?

34:39.413 --> 34:41.076
Say it with me, repent.

34:41.256 --> 34:42.057
What is repentance?

34:42.177 --> 34:43.319
It's doing a 180.

34:44.862 --> 34:46.725
It's turning around on the highway of life.

34:47.666 --> 34:55.860
It's saying, I'm going the wrong way, living in my own kingdom, living in my own kingdom, and I need to stop, and I need to turn into the kingdom, which is very, very near.

34:57.763 --> 34:59.666
And it's what I was made for.

34:59.906 --> 35:02.629
It's like a fish out of water jumping into the water.

35:02.769 --> 35:04.170
I'm finally home.

35:06.513 --> 35:08.275
And as a church, we've been handed the ball.

35:08.295 --> 35:14.962
It's like Jesus, when he ascended back to heaven, he handed it off to us and said, now that I've fulfilled my mission, here's what I want you to do.

35:14.982 --> 35:17.124
I want you to go out and invite others into the kingdom.

35:18.185 --> 35:19.687
And so as a church, that's what we've been doing.

35:19.727 --> 35:21.248
We call it the relentless pursuit.

35:22.109 --> 35:24.292
We're here to see people come to Christ and grow in Christ.

35:24.312 --> 35:25.633
So what does it mean to you today?

35:25.693 --> 35:26.674
Two challenges.

35:26.754 --> 35:30.521
Number one in your notes there is you need to follow Jesus yourself into the kingdom.

35:32.766 --> 35:34.269
You need to follow Jesus yourself.

35:34.750 --> 35:35.511
You need to go in.

35:35.872 --> 35:38.617
You need to find the treasure hidden in the field.

35:39.599 --> 35:40.721
You need to experience it.

35:40.942 --> 35:41.463
Live in it.

35:41.483 --> 35:42.585
Absorb it.

35:43.567 --> 35:44.188
Walk with him.

35:44.248 --> 35:45.170
Talk with him.

35:45.602 --> 35:59.730
live under his active rule, find the treasure yourself, and what happens is he begins to transform you from the inside out, and anger begins to fall off, and lust begins to fall off, and greed begins to fall away from your life.

36:00.162 --> 36:03.789
Addictions fall away from your life, not at first, but over time.

36:04.029 --> 36:13.707
And what gets replaced is this thing called the fruit of the Spirit, this love and joy and peace and patience and kindness and gentleness and self-control begin to dominate your life.

36:13.788 --> 36:19.919
And we're reformed from the inside out as we live in God's kingdom under his active role.

36:20.300 --> 36:21.522
We have to seek it.

36:21.954 --> 36:23.796
We have to find it and live in it.

36:23.816 --> 36:27.100
Jesus gave us this instruction in Matthew chapter 6 verse 33.

36:27.741 --> 36:30.805
Seek the kingdom of God above all else.

36:31.706 --> 36:39.476
Before you do any other seeking in your life, promotions at work or having another child or finding a new home or moving away or whatever.

36:39.696 --> 36:42.740
Before you seek anything else in life, I want you to seek the kingdom.

36:43.841 --> 36:44.362
What does that mean?

36:44.722 --> 36:45.203
Live in it.

36:45.663 --> 36:51.090
And he promises, if we do that and we live righteously, he will give you everything that you need.

36:52.386 --> 36:54.851
If we don't do number one, guess what?

36:55.513 --> 37:11.346
We won't be excited to do number two, which is to invite others into the kingdom, to do what Cindy's been doing, to do what Levi did, and say, you got to come, you got to come, you got to hear.

37:12.450 --> 37:15.976
See, I never said to Cindy, Cindy, I'm glad you're coming to church, Tom.

37:16.256 --> 37:26.033
I didn't call them in and have a little meeting with them and say, now that you love Emmanuel and Ross invited you and I'm so glad he did, now you need to go and invite everybody else in your life.

37:26.614 --> 37:27.616
I never said that to them.

37:28.197 --> 37:29.118
I never said that to her.

37:30.601 --> 37:31.723
She did it by herself, why?

37:31.983 --> 37:38.354
Because when you find the kingdom and you realize what you found, that you found hidden treasure in a field

37:38.530 --> 37:44.396
In your excitement, in your joy, you naturally invite others into what you are enjoying, yes?

37:44.797 --> 37:47.820
See, the reason why some of you haven't invited some, can I say something hard?

37:48.060 --> 37:48.681
Can I do that, yes?

37:49.041 --> 37:49.482
Can I do that?

37:50.603 --> 37:51.204
Just bracing you.

37:52.886 --> 37:59.072
The reason some of you haven't invited anyone in the last two months, six months, two years, five years to church.

37:59.433 --> 38:06.440
The reason it's all about you and you barely come is because you're not living in the kingdom.

38:06.661 --> 38:07.922
Why would you invite others into it?

38:10.018 --> 38:11.420
There's not excitement, there's not joy.

38:11.961 --> 38:13.302
You see how important number one is?

38:13.483 --> 38:17.708
You have to live in it with Jesus, walk with him, talk with him.

38:20.833 --> 38:26.460
Surrender your kingdom to his kingdom and then that joy takes over and you're like, maybe I've gotta get everybody else involved in this.

38:28.643 --> 38:29.485
And you invite others in.

38:29.545 --> 38:32.268
Jesus' message was very, very simple to his disciples.

38:32.328 --> 38:34.171
Watch this in Matthew chapter four, verse 19.

38:34.612 --> 38:38.056
He called his disciples to him and said, follow me and here's what I'm gonna do.

38:38.116 --> 38:39.378
I'm gonna show you how to,

38:39.714 --> 38:40.595
fish for people.

38:40.615 --> 38:42.037
Today we're fishing for fish.

38:43.138 --> 38:43.899
That was their job.

38:44.559 --> 38:46.922
Jesus says, now that you're in, here's what we're going to do.

38:46.942 --> 38:48.103
We're going to catch some people.

38:48.143 --> 38:54.510
We're going to be on a relentless pursuit to invite as many people as possible into the kingdom.

38:54.530 --> 38:56.993
So number one, live in the kingdom yourself.

38:57.073 --> 39:03.300
Follow Jesus into the kingdom and invite others into it so that they can partake.

39:03.840 --> 39:05.362
So right now, I want you to think of three people.

39:07.298 --> 39:11.003
Just three people in your proximity, maybe someone at work, maybe it's someone in your home.

39:12.625 --> 39:14.107
Maybe it's someone you run into at the bank.

39:15.749 --> 39:17.892
Maybe it's a barista at your favorite coffee shop.

39:18.453 --> 39:19.755
They are a fish out of water right now.

39:19.795 --> 39:25.463
They're flopping around, trapped in anxiety, fear, worry, trapped in pursuing money or wealth.

39:26.184 --> 39:28.106
You know who they are, just think of three people.

39:28.266 --> 39:31.311
John, Sue, why is it always Sue?

39:31.451 --> 39:32.652
I don't know why it's always Sue.

39:32.813 --> 39:35.897
Sue, there's a lot of Sue's out there, I don't know.

39:35.917 --> 39:36.818
Maybe it's a Kevin.

39:38.210 --> 39:40.493
Maybe it's a Sam or a Samantha, I don't know.

39:41.895 --> 39:44.338
They're fish out of water right now, because that's how it is.

39:44.679 --> 39:53.071
People were made designed to live in the kingdom and they're outside and their gills are going like this and they're going, they're not dead yet.

39:54.332 --> 39:57.657
But if they stay outside of the kingdom, they will die physically and spiritually.

39:58.698 --> 39:59.419
What are their names?

40:01.322 --> 40:02.243
Go ahead and think of them right now.

40:05.708 --> 40:07.090
God wants to use you to reach them.

40:07.874 --> 40:11.221
God is calling you to be on a relentless pursuit to help them enter into the kingdom.

40:14.308 --> 40:21.984
And so, during this last song, I'm going to invite you, during this song, every single one of you, my hope, is to get up out of your seat.

40:22.385 --> 40:26.834
And there's name boards, whatever campus you're at, there's name boards all along the back walls.

40:27.042 --> 40:28.704
here at Greenwood, there are two in the balcony.

40:28.824 --> 40:29.585
See those name boards?

40:30.206 --> 40:31.006
It's not graffiti.

40:31.747 --> 40:33.709
We don't write on our walls for the sake of writing on our walls.

40:34.110 --> 40:39.035
We write names down of people that we all, that you all are relentlessly pursuing.

40:39.055 --> 40:44.101
Over here, there's a name board, whatever campus that you're at, there's a name board.

40:44.121 --> 40:54.453
And during this song, I would love for you in a response to this talk to get up out of your seat and write those names on the board that you, people you are going to pursue.

40:54.733 --> 40:55.634
Christmas is coming.

40:56.578 --> 40:58.720
Here at Emmanuel, it's a great time to invite your friends.

41:00.042 --> 41:03.366
It gets almost American to come to church during Christmas, yes?

41:05.468 --> 41:08.952
So it's very easy to get a friend to come to a service during Christmas time.

41:11.676 --> 41:14.799
Will you pray with me and then will you rise and will you write their names on the boards?

41:14.819 --> 41:15.300
Will we do that?

41:15.360 --> 41:15.820
Can you do that?

41:16.521 --> 41:16.902
Pray with me.

41:18.684 --> 41:24.050
Father, thank you for the clarity of the mission of your son.

41:25.058 --> 41:26.720
that he didn't come for the healthy people.

41:26.760 --> 41:29.583
He didn't come for those who think they're righteous and have it all together.

41:29.623 --> 41:31.085
He came for the Levi's.

41:34.108 --> 41:37.031
The people who know they're going the wrong direction.

41:37.812 --> 41:41.256
Me.

41:41.276 --> 41:48.604
And you came to encourage us to do a 180 to repent and step into life with you.

41:50.386 --> 41:54.130
And so help us right now, have enough courage to rise out of our seat

41:54.946 --> 41:59.092
and to write the names down of the people that are in our life.

42:00.394 --> 42:15.417
Not famous celebrities, people will never talk to, but people on the job, in our classroom, our next door neighbors, to relentlessly pursue them, to invite them into the kingdom.

42:16.979 --> 42:21.746
Give us success, give us boldness, give us courage, give us wisdom as we pursue them.

42:22.530 --> 42:33.582
Maybe, maybe today, as you heard me describing the invitation, you suddenly realized, oh my gosh, I'm Levi.

42:33.602 --> 42:37.947
Like, I have been pursuing all the wrong things.

42:39.389 --> 42:45.916
Things that I know will never ultimately satisfy my soul first.

42:45.936 --> 42:48.018
Maybe that's where you found yourself today.

42:50.946 --> 42:52.769
And you need to hear this message.

42:53.229 --> 42:53.550
You.

42:55.392 --> 42:56.454
You are invited.

42:57.295 --> 42:59.819
You personally are invited to follow Jesus.

43:02.262 --> 43:10.534
Jesus has said to you, regardless of going down the wrong path and chasing all the wrong things, you may come.

43:12.277 --> 43:13.499
You may enter in.

43:16.783 --> 43:18.546
And today you need to make that choice.

43:19.554 --> 43:21.798
And you know it in your heart and you know who you are.

43:23.160 --> 43:28.288
You've avoided it long enough and now God's calling you in and he's even drawing you in and you can sense it.

43:29.770 --> 43:30.752
This is your moment.

43:33.015 --> 43:36.681
This is your time to do business with God.

43:38.544 --> 43:40.807
And if that's you right now, I'm just gonna say a simple prayer.

43:41.148 --> 43:42.109
It's a prayer of faith.

43:43.331 --> 43:45.455
It's a prayer of courage.

43:46.316 --> 43:47.538
It's a prayer of trust.

43:48.450 --> 43:54.236
It's a prayer declaring that you're turning, you're repenting, and you're stepping into God's kingdom.

43:55.917 --> 43:57.879
And you can take these words and you can make them your own.

43:57.939 --> 43:59.981
You don't even have to come up with the prayer yourself.

44:01.363 --> 44:05.467
It's not even the words, it's the faith behind the words.

44:05.487 --> 44:09.330
And if that's you right now, do business with God.

44:11.753 --> 44:14.655
Say this to him.

44:14.675 --> 44:17.298
Dear Jesus, thank you.

44:18.146 --> 44:19.368
for not passing me by.

44:24.035 --> 44:34.512
Thank you for stopping today and extending the invitation to me to follow you, to step into life with you.

44:37.296 --> 44:42.164
It's what I've been looking for, hoping for, longing for.

44:44.127 --> 44:46.290
And so today I turn

44:47.458 --> 44:51.742
I do a 180 into your kingdom.

44:53.784 --> 44:58.169
I believe that you sacrificed your life to make that possible.

44:59.230 --> 45:09.980
You died in a cross to provide grace and forgiveness for all of my sins, mistakes, and wrongdoings.

45:10.000 --> 45:13.544
So I embrace that grace today.

45:13.564 --> 45:14.024
Wash me.

45:15.445 --> 45:15.986
Cleanse me.

45:17.442 --> 45:18.343
and make me your child.

45:20.286 --> 45:38.213
And from this day forward, teach me to seek your kingdom, to live in it, bathe in it, soak in it, experience all that you have for me, and help me to invite others in as well.

45:38.233 --> 45:39.415
And I pray this in Christ's name.

45:39.935 --> 45:41.999
And everybody said, amen.

45:42.139 --> 45:44.002
Can we give God glory to our Amen?

45:44.022 --> 45:47.026
Come on, all of our campuses, amen.

45:48.706 --> 45:55.002
If you trusted Christ right now, if you entered into the kingdom, whatever campus you're at in the back, there'll be these little Bibles you can grab.

45:55.022 --> 45:57.649
There's folks to my right to my left in the back of your campus.

45:57.949 --> 45:59.794
They love to put a New Testament in your hands.

